# Maven Prototype Playground — Prototype Rules

## Project structure

- Each designer has a directory under `src/app/{designer}/` (e.g. `src/app/taylor/`)
- Each prototype is a subdirectory: `src/app/{designer}/{slug}/`
- Every prototype has two files: `metadata.json` (gallery info) and `page.tsx` (the UI)
- Pages must use `"use client"` since they contain interactive components

## Consumer (Freya) prototypes

### Components

Always import from the barrel file:

```tsx
import { FreyaNavBar, FreyaTabBar, FreyaTaskCard, ... } from "@/components/freya";
```

Available components:
- `FreyaNavBar` — top navigation bar with Maven logo
- `FreyaTabBar` — horizontal tab bar (`tabs={["Home", "Rx", "Care"]} activeTab="Home"`)
- `FreyaButton` — primary/secondary buttons (`variant="primary"` or `variant="secondary"`)
- `FreyaBadge` — status badges (`variant="maven"`, `variant="success"`, `variant="neutral"`)
- `FreyaTaskCard` — action cards with overline, badge, title, description, CTA buttons
- `FreyaAppointmentCard` — provider appointment cards (providerName, specialty, dateTime)
- `FreyaContentCard` — article/content cards (badge, subjectTag, title, timeLabel)
- `FreyaSupportCard` — support contact cards (title, subtitle, ctaLabel, icon)
- `FreyaAccordion` — expandable sections with icon items
- `FreyaSectionHeader` — section titles with optional action link or search
- `FreyaCarousel` — horizontal scrolling container with dot indicators
- `FreyaFooter` — bottom footer with Maven branding

### Screen wrapper

Always wrap Consumer screens in `ScreenShell`:

```tsx
import { ScreenShell } from "@/components/screen/ScreenShell";

export default function MyScreen() {
  return (
    <ScreenShell>
      <FreyaNavBar />
      <FreyaTabBar tabs={["Home", "Rx", "Care"]} activeTab="Home" />
      <div className="px-4 flex flex-col gap-6 pb-6">
        {/* Content here */}
      </div>
      <FreyaFooter />
    </ScreenShell>
  );
}
```

### Design tokens (CSS variables)

- Colors: `var(--color-b2c-text-primary)`, `var(--color-b2c-text-secondary)`, `var(--color-b2c-text-tertiary)`, `var(--color-b2c-text-link)`, `var(--color-b2c-surface-primary)`, `var(--color-b2c-border-primary)`, `var(--color-b2c-border-disabled)`, `var(--color-b2c-icon-primary)`, `var(--color-b2c-icon-maven)`
- Headings: use `fontFamily: "var(--font-family-b2c-emphasis)"` (Ivar Display) for display headings
- Body text: uses `var(--font-family-sans)` automatically via ScreenShell
- Border radius: `var(--b2c-radius-sm)`, `var(--b2c-radius-md)`, `var(--b2c-radius-lg)`

### Typography pattern for headings

```tsx
<h1 style={{
  fontSize: 34,
  lineHeight: 1.2,
  fontFamily: "var(--font-family-b2c-emphasis)",
  color: "var(--color-b2c-text-primary)",
  fontWeight: 400,
}}>
  Welcome, <em style={{ fontStyle: "italic" }}>Kate</em>
</h1>
```

### Reference screens

Look at these files for high-quality examples:
- `src/screens/home.tsx` — Home screen with task cards, carousels, support
- `src/screens/care-glp1.tsx` — Care screen with appointments, accordion, content
- `src/screens/rx.tsx` — Rx screen with list/detail views and local state

## Enterprise (MDL) prototypes

### Components

Always import from the barrel file:

```tsx
import { MdlHeader, MdlButton, MdlCard, MdlAlert, ... } from "@/components/enterprise";
```

Available components:
- `MdlButton` — primary/secondary/ghost/destructive buttons (`variant`, `size="sm"|"md"|"lg"`, `disabled`)
- `MdlTextInput` — text input with label, error, disabled states (`label`, `placeholder`, `error`, `disabled`)
- `MdlBadge` — status badges (`variant="maven"|"success"|"warning"|"error"|"attention"|"neutral"`, `label`)
- `MdlCard` — content card with title, description, children, optional onClick
- `MdlAlert` — inline alert with icon (`variant="success"|"warning"|"error"|"info"`, `title`, `message`, `onDismiss`)
- `MdlHeader` — app header with Maven logo (`title`, `actions`)
- `MdlFooter` — simple footer with Maven branding
- `MdlAvatar` — circle avatar with initials fallback (`name`, `src`, `size="sm"|"md"|"lg"`)
- `MdlListItem` — list row with label, value, optional chevron (`label`, `value`, `onClick`)
- `MdlModal` — overlay dialog (`title`, `children`, `onClose`, `actions`)

### Screen wrapper

Always wrap Enterprise screens in `EnterpriseShell`:

```tsx
import { EnterpriseShell } from "@/components/screen/EnterpriseShell";

export default function MyScreen() {
  return (
    <EnterpriseShell>
      <MdlHeader title="Dashboard" />
      <div style={{ padding: 16, display: "flex", flexDirection: "column", gap: 16 }}>
        {/* Content here */}
      </div>
      <MdlFooter />
    </EnterpriseShell>
  );
}
```

### Design tokens (CSS variables)

- Text: `var(--color-enterprise-text-primary)`, `var(--color-enterprise-text-secondary)`, `var(--color-enterprise-text-tertiary)`, `var(--color-enterprise-text-link)`, `var(--color-enterprise-text-error)`
- Icon: `var(--color-enterprise-icon-primary)`, `var(--color-enterprise-icon-maven)`, `var(--color-enterprise-icon-success)`
- Surface: `var(--color-enterprise-surface-primary)`, `var(--color-enterprise-surface-secondary)`, `var(--color-enterprise-surface-tertiary)`, `var(--color-enterprise-surface-brand)`
- Fill: `var(--color-enterprise-fill-button-primary)`, `var(--color-enterprise-fill-accent-mint)`, `var(--color-enterprise-fill-accent-brand)`
- Border: `var(--color-enterprise-border-primary)`, `var(--color-enterprise-border-natural)`, `var(--color-enterprise-border-brand)`, `var(--color-enterprise-border-input-focus)`
- Headings: use `fontFamily: "var(--font-family-enterprise-emphasis)"` (Ivar Display) for display headings
- Body text: uses `var(--font-family-sans)` automatically via EnterpriseShell

### Typography pattern for headings

```tsx
<h1 style={{
  fontSize: 28,
  lineHeight: 1.2,
  fontFamily: "var(--font-family-enterprise-emphasis)",
  color: "var(--color-enterprise-text-primary)",
  fontWeight: 400,
  fontStyle: "italic",
}}>
  Member Dashboard
</h1>
```

## Maven Assistant (chat) prototypes

### Layout

- The chat shell is always 375px wide (mobile-first, matching iOS viewport). Never create wider layouts for the chat view.
- The gallery page (`/`) is full-width desktop.

### Components

All chat UI components live in `src/components/chat/`. Always import from the barrel:

```tsx
import { ChatShell, MessageBubble, SmartCard, ... } from "@/components/chat";
```

Available components:
- `ChatShell` — full chat view (title, turns, variant tabs)
- `MessageBubble` — single message (agent/user/medical-team)
- `Composer` — input bar
- `PromptHScroll` — horizontal scrolling prompt suggestions
- `ChipAction` — tappable chip
- `SmartCard` — appointment/booking/escalation cards
- `EscalationCard` — handoff to support card
- `ThreadRow` — conversation list row
- `MavenOrb` — animated Maven avatar
- `GlassLayer` — frosted glass overlay (`backdrop-blur-xl bg-white/70`)
- `GradientBackground` — chat gradient backdrop

Never inline chat UI styles — reuse these components. If a new component type is needed, add it to `src/components/chat/` and export it from `index.ts`.

### Scenarios

- Chat prototypes are defined as `Scenario` objects in `src/scenarios/` (see `src/lib/scenario-types.ts` for the type).
- After creating a scenario file, import and register it in `src/lib/prototype-registry.ts`.
- Templates have `isTemplate: true` (shown in the Templates tab). Prototypes have `isTemplate: false`.
- Use `src/scenarios/_template.ts` as the base structure for new scenarios.

### Variants

- Scenarios support `variants?: Record<string, Turn[]>` for branch points.
- Common variant names: "Clarifying question", "Source cards", "Error / recovery", "Escalation".
- `ChatShell` renders variant tabs automatically when variants are present.

### Styling

- Font family: Helvetica Neue (set in `globals.css`, do not override).
- Use Tailwind utility classes with `maven-*` color tokens.

## When asked to create a new prototype

1. If `metadata.json` already exists, create/edit `page.tsx` in the same directory.
2. Choose Consumer (ScreenShell + Freya), Enterprise (EnterpriseShell + Mdl), or Maven Assistant (ChatShell) based on the request.
3. For chat prototypes: create a scenario file in `src/scenarios/`, then register it in `src/lib/prototype-registry.ts`.
4. Use real, specific content — not placeholder lorem ipsum.
5. Use existing components before building custom UI.
6. Test at `http://localhost:3000/{designer}/{slug}`.
